# NABH â€“ IT & Digital Health Controls

NABH accreditation requires hospitals to demonstrate
robust IT governance and data protection mechanisms.

## Key IT Control Areas
- User access management
- Authentication & authorization
- Audit logging & traceability
- Backup and recovery
- Downtime procedures

## Evidence Typically Reviewed
- Access control policies
- User role matrices
- Backup logs & restore reports
- Incident & escalation records
- Vendor contracts & SLAs

## Best Practice
Align IT controls with clinical workflows to ensure
compliance without operational disruption.
